# Up Final Blueprint (Global Constitution)

1. Primary workspace is `up-final`; `reference-app`, `reference-app-fitness`, and `lbj-goat-meter` are read-only references.
2. Business model is fixed:
   - Core App: one-time purchase unlocks all local features (assessment, 6-axis radar, personal history, widgets).
   - Pro Service: monthly subscription unlocks leaderboard participation and cloud sync.
3. Local-first is mandatory:
   - Arm size and grip strength data must remain fully usable without subscription.
   - Personal detailed history must not be blocked behind Pro.
4. Access control is mandatory in `src/logic/core`:
   - Centralize entitlement checks for core access and Pro access.
   - Leaderboard actions require valid Pro status.
5. Firebase cost guardrails are mandatory:
   - Non-Pro users must not generate Firestore leaderboard read/write traffic.
   - Leaderboard stores summary data only (best score + minimal profile fields).
   - Enforce leaderboard caching and write throttling.
6. Architecture discipline:
   - Keep separation across `logic` / `services` / `stores` / `hooks` / `components`.
   - UI stays presentational; business logic and SDK calls stay out of components.
7. Scoring roadmap:
   - Preserve existing arm-size scoring.
   - Add grip-strength scoring.
   - Radar chart must support six dimensions.
